OL,3,GBLOOPERSCPower cut disrupts S4C
OL,4,CEisteddfod coverage
OL,5,
OL,6,FThis afternoon's live coverage of
OL,7,FEisteddfod yr Urdd on S4C was disrupted
OL,8,Ffor a time due to a power failure at
OL,9,Fthe site.
OL,11,FAt the point where the power cut out,
OL,12,Fvision froze and audio dropped
OL,13,Fcompletely.
OL,15,FAfter about 25 seconds, S4C playout cut
OL,16,Fto a prerecorded compilation of visuals
OL,17,Ffrom the Eisteddfod, which included a
OL,18,Ftext-based apology for the
OL,19,Finterruption, in English and Welsh.
OL,23,EPub: 25-May-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,155,140,200,120,0,100
PN,15402
SC,0002
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F154A1783631508
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G2/2
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GBLOOPERSCPower cut disrupts S4C
OL,4,CEisteddfod coverage
OL,5,
OL,6,FThis sequence had no audio. Though the
OL,7,Flive announcer provided regular verbal
OL,8,Fapologies.
OL,10,FAfter just under a minute, playout cut
OL,11,Fto a live shot showing much of the
OL,12,FEisteddfod site. Again, there was no
OL,13,Faudio, apart from regular verbal
OL,14,Fapologies from the announcer.
OL,16,FAfter about four-and-a-half minutes,
OL,17,Fthe first of two short filler
OL,18,Fprogrammes appeared.
OL,20,FAnd just under seventeen minutes after
OL,21,Fthe power went out, we were returned to
OL,22,Fthe live coverage.
OL,23,EPub: 25-May-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
